Sun Java System OpenSSO: famAdminTools.zip 
====================================================

This file contains information on installing and using famAdminTools.zip.
It is assumed that Federated Access Manager Server is available.

Table of contents:
-----------------
1. Supported versions of Java Runtime
2. Installing famAdminTools.zip
3. What does this package contain?

1. Supported versions of Java Runtime
-------------------------
J2SE 1.5 or higher.

2. Installing famAdminTools.zip
------------------------------ 

Steps involved in installing famAdminTools.zip are:

Step 1: Unzip famAdminTools.zip to the desired directory.

Step 2: Go to the directory which has the famAdminTools.zip unzipped.
        Run the setup command as follows:
        "./setup" or "setup"
        for Unix and Windows respectively.
        Then enter the configuration directory when prompted.
        "Path to config files of Federated Access Manager
        (example: /fam_config/opensso):"

Step 3: After step 2 is performed, the CLIs can be run under the following
        directory:
        <TOOLS_DIR>/<FAM_INSTANCE_NAME>/bin
        where <TOOLS_DIR> is the directory which has famAdminTools.zip unzipped
        (ie: current directory), and <FAM_INSTANCE_NAME> is the deployment
        URI of Federated Access Manager.
        
